This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically cross-domain detection. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning models and regularization techniques, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves the use of relational graphs, which are commonly used in robotics and computer vision, making cs.RO (Robotics) a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves experiments with synthetic data, which is commonly used in multimedia applications, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category as well.
